<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<class name="PBDSolver" inherits="RefCounted" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/godotengine/godot/master/doc/class.xsd">
	<brief_description>
		Position-based dynamics chain solver. The physics engine inside a [Tentacle].
	</brief_description>
	<description>
		Holds an array of mass particles connected by distance + bending constraints, plus optional anchor / soft target / pose / collision projections (§3 of the architecture doc). One [Tentacle] node owns one [PBDSolver]; the Tentacle's exports are forwarding setters on this instance.
		Direct access is exposed for tests + tooling. Normal authoring should go through the Tentacle's @exports.
	</description>
